- PKCE challenge (S256), state (CSRF), client_id all present in auth URL
- Callback server receives real HTTP GET at `http://localhost:53692/callback?code=...&state=...`, verifies state match, responds HTTP 200 with success HTML
- CLI starts normally (`exit 0`) with `OPENCLAW_OAUTH_CALLBACK_HOST=0.0.0.0` — import safety proven
- Helper functions still reject non-loopback hosts and accept all three loopback addresses with correct URL derivation

**What was not tested:**
- Live Anthropic OAuth token exchange (requires real credentials and browser)
